title: Kate Middleton is not pregnant despite rumors claiming Duchess of Cambridge is expecting third child
text:
Tweet 
After four months since Duchess of Cambridge, née Kate Middleton, welcomed daughter Princess Charlotte, rumors of a third royal baby being on the way have surfaced lately. 
A source cited by Star magazine told the publication that the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge will become parents again, as the British royal mother-of-two is pregnant again. 
Gossip Cop denied the Duchess’ third pregnancy, citing a palace source saying that the report is “not true.” 
Kate gave birth to her and William’s second child on May 2, although her due date was in late April. Royal fans eagerly awaited the arrival of the second child, who is the fourth in the order of succession to the British throne, as many of them camped outside the Lindo Wing at St. Mary’s Hospital for weeks. 
In an interview to Sky News in July, Prince William was asked if he and his wife are thinking about having another child. 
“We’ve only just had the second one. You never know what is going to happen in the future,” the Duke said then. Until an official confirmation, the speculation about a possible third pregnancy should be taken with a grain of salt. Spread the rumor
